					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Jeremiah.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="142v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Yirme῾yahu</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש ירמיהו </title>
							<note>
								<p>Concerns Jeremiah 26:20-27:5 and 33:17-52:31.</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text only the opening word or words of each verse are given, an Arabic translation being added.</p>
								<p>Has a number of masoretic notes.</p>
								<p>The later folios (13-26) embody the full Hebrew text of chapters 35:6-36:31, the vowel-points being added for the most part.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Sabih_2009"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of approximately 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>142 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>133</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>162</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>142 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>15 quires of originally 10 leaves each. 3 quires are currently incomplete.</p>
									<p>Signatures in Hebrew letters on the righ-hand upper corner of the first page, now wholly or partially lost.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folios 3, 127, 128, 136, 137, 139-141 have been more or less mutilated; of folios 138 and 142 only small portions are preserved.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Has masoretic and other notes in the margins.</p>
									<p>Visible ruling with a hard-point.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Oriental square script of approximately 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="13r" to="26v"/>- supplied by a later hand.</p>
							</handNote>
